description.0: Trapped in Attilan! The Fantastic Four find themselves at the mercy of the Inhuman known as Maximus the Mad! But how can they possibly defeat him...when they've been shrunk down to a mere fraction of their size!?
description.7: Spider-Man tries to clear the name of Peter Parker, but will Detective Raven be convinced? Meanwhile, there's trouble on the home front with MJ, her unborn child, and Aunt May!
description.8: The Avengers follow the Red Skull to the island where strange EMP readings had been discovered. But as soon as the team hits the shore, they face an attack from A.I.M. adaptoids! Plus, Captain America finds his body restored after Superia works magic. Featuring A.I.M.'s favorite automation, M.O.D.O.K.!
description.9: Captain America versus A.I.M.! Cap leads Free Spirit, Falcon, and Jack Flag in the Avengers first Strike against A.I.M.!
description.10: Attilan destroyed! Thor vs Namor! Atlantis under attack! What can the Fantastic Four do to stem the chaos?
description.11: After the destruction of Attilan, the Crimson Cadre look to take their revenge on Earth. Can Fantastic Force halt their mayhem?
description.13: Han Solo'and'Princess'Leia'have taken refuge with'their twins'on the'planet'New Alderaan. But refuge, it seems, eludes the family when Emperor Palpatine and an AT-AT battalion come hunting for Rebel officers. Worry not, Leia! They don't want your lives, they just want your children!
description.14: Artoo-Detoo'and'See-Threepio'may have bitten off more than they can chew! Their boss has been blown to bits, and they're marooned in perhaps the most dangerous place in the universe:'Nar Shaddaa! The beautiful and deadly'Jace Forno'has somehow wormed her mercenary self into the spaceport's top security position, and it seems like she's got an agenda for taking care of all kinds of meddlesome'droids!
description.21: Moondragon lies gravely injured, and so Adam must bestow the Mind Gem onto another. Maxam offers to bear it, but Gamora isn't letting him have it without a fight!
description.24: Strange usually has control of every situation, but not when he's kidnapped by a group of thugs!
description.27: Hulk and Betty's peaceful getaway is turning into a not-so-peaceful thriller! Between hospital ambushes and clashes with superhuman police chiefs, can Hulk keep it together before Savage Banner takes over?
description.28: While Iron Man, Black Widow, and Crimson Dynamo battle Titanium Man, Tony's mentor Ted Slaght is killed in a laboratory accident.
description.29: Mary Jane's life hangs in the balance...unless Kaine is taken care of- permanently!
description.30: Thor and Sif continue to impress New Yorkers. Kurse, the new ruler of Hel, touches down on Earth!
description.31: Spidey's wrongfully imprisoned! Can a solo Ben Reilly stand triumphant against Kaine?
description.32: A special 64-page anniversary issue! Aron the Rogue Watcher plucks villains from across the timestream to destroy the FF once and for all! But Aron himself must contend with one that is his equal - Uatu, Earth's true Watcher! Then, when the dust has settled, the Fantastic Four at last pay final respects to their dear friend and leader, Reed Richards.
description.33: Peter Parker's cloned monstrosities are on the loose! Will Spider-Man and Scarlet Spider escape with their lives?
description.39: Black Brigade has returned, and he won't stop until he exacts his revenge on every member of Force Works! His first target - Julia Carpenter, aka Spider-Woman!
description.40: The symbiote showdown continues! Law enforcement has no effect on the rampaging Carnage, which means it's time for Venom to enter the fray! But can even Venom muster the savage strength he needs to put down a monster like Carnage?
description.42: Namor at the mercy of magic!
description.47: Why is Peter Parker on the lam? And how will Spider-Man recover given last issue's devastation?
description.48: The Red Skull takes out the Avengers with his "divide and conquer" strategy. Although Black Widow proves to be the most formidable opponent, Red Skull escapes after discovering another EMP abnormality. Could this be the return of the Cosmic Cube?
description.49: Death-Stalker stalks the Sentinel of Liberty as he unravels the mystery of the new Super-Patriot and the diabolical dead ringer!
description.50: Dominic shares his intertwined memory with Sorcerer Supreme, Doctor Strange! Walter recounts a wartime tale...
description.51: Lando Calrissian's'X-1 Viper War Droids'have painted a target on the'Emperor's'citadel, but an army of'monstrous creatures'are making it their own mission to stop the'New Republic'fighters. Meanwhile, on the'world'of'Ganath,'Han Solo'has to equip his damaged'Millennium Falcon'with antique weaponry. Will it be enough to escape from'Boba Fett?'
description.52: Introducing Boba Fett, the nastiest bounty hunter this side of the galaxy! Who is the man feared by both the Empire and the Rebels? And why has he trapped Han and Luke in an icy tundra?
description.53: Olag Greck'is a con man and arch criminal, and he's hiding out exactly where you might expect: among his own, wretched kind on the'smugglerplanet'Nar Shaddaa. But knowing where he is and actually arresting him are two completely different matters as the newly-deputized'Artoo-Detoo'and See-Threepio'discover. Smugglers and criminals have no affection for old droids, particularly when they're carrying badges! They're just a couple of used appliances in hot pursuit of a perp, and a world of accomplices stand in their way!
description.61: Domitian's sinister plan is revealed, and the fate of Infinity Watch hangs in the balance. Can even the help of newly reformed Zakaius stop his master's evil?
description.63: Sinister has disappeared and Cyclops is given his old job. Havok's jealousy grows. How will this affect the brother's relationship and what does it hold for the future of Apocalypse's army?
description.64: Doctor Strange must destroy Salome's nest in Times Square!
description.65: Jabba'the'Hutt'lives to negotiate, and the art of the deal is his only discipline. But the goods he trades are the lives of others, and in that line of business you can't lose your head. In this self-contained story, Jabba finds himself bartering with'Gaar'Suppoon, rumored to be an absolute devil at the negotiating table. There's a valuable lesson to be learned here: In a deal with the devil, you can always refuse. In a deal with Jabba, it's not advised.
description.67: Force Works and Dreamguard continue their deadly battle with the creature known only as the Orphan! Plus, a who's who of Marvel heroes remembers their fallen comrade, Wonder Man.
description.68: Carnage has had enough of captivity at Ravencroft Institute, so he's broken free and is eager to rekindle his spree of violence. One only person knows the symbiote well enough to stop him - Eddie Brock, better known to the world as Venom!
description.70: A follower of Apocalypse has infiltrated the X-villain's archives. This is your peek into the mutants of the Age of Apocalypse, those who are allies of En Sabah Nur...and those who are freedom fighters for a peaceful tomorrow. A great introduction to the X-Men of the dystopian future!
description.75: Hulk gets closer to discovering the secert of the missing children!
description.76: Tony Stark throws down with Titanium Man!
description.77: Questions are answered concerning the third Peter Parker. Scarlet Spider swings alone against Kaine!
description.78: Lorelei and Malekith persuade the Thing to drink enchanted mead!
description.79: Spider-Man and Scarlet Spider get some conflicting information regarding their identities. Aunt May's condition takes an upturn!
description.80: The Dark Raider strikes! The Rogue Watcher plots! The FF face off with the Crimson Cadre! And Susan Storm is locked in a fight to the death - with an alternate evil Reed Richards!
description.81: Our hero is imprisoned on a murder charge! The Jackal makes his escape from Ravencroft.
description.86: Spider-Man swings in for the rescue! The Web-head offers an assist to Rory and Pandora in order to save Sam and Kay!
description.87: Using the Ebony Blade doesn't come without a price and Namor is learning that hard fact first hand.
description.89: The status quo of Peter Parker's life is shaken to the core in this Anniversary Special. Featuring a tale penned by Stan "The Man" Lee! Plus, the origin of Ben Reilly!
description.90: The Black Widow follows a tip received from an old friend. In the Canadian Northwest, a strange energy pulse has alerted the Avengers' attention. Could the Black Widow's tip and the peculiar energy readings be connected? Featuring the return of the Red Skull!
description.91: Without his new armor he would lie paralyzed! With it, he intends to go out in a blaze of glory. Captain America marches on!
description.92: In the fourth chapter of'this epic series,'Luke Skywalker'discovers'an ancient, powerful Jedi relic'among the ruins of theplanet'Ossus. But can he get off the planet with it, or even with his life? The'Emperor's'Darksiders'are hot on Luke's tail, and he must battle for his life before he can battle for'the galaxy!
description.93: Tun Wala cements their place as the galaxy's seediest planet when they sell ship parts to both the Rebels and the Empire. With their X-Wings' severely compromised by Imperial forces, will the Rebels be able to rely on spare parts from Tun Wala? Plus, Darth Vader enters the fray against the Alliance!
description.94: In the final, climactic issue of this landmark series, two renegade Jedi, Ulic Qel-Droma and Exar Kun, clash in mortal combat. One will be awarded the title of Dark Lord of the Sith, the most feared and powerful force in the galaxy; the other may be awarded a shallow grave. The fate of the entire universe rests on the outcome!

2.text: Age of Apocalypse! Wolverine versus the X-Men! Plus, a love triangle forms between Rogue, Gambit, and Magneto!

5.text: Although new in his usurped office, Doctor Doom, President of the United States, sets new plans in motion to target the corporate greed of the 1%... with deadly repercussions.

6.text: Something strange is happening to Jean Grey…

12.text: Elektra is faced with an ex-lover and must fight the Hand and the sinister Snakeroot.

21.text: Moondragon lies gravely injured, and so Adam must bestow the Mind Gem onto another. Maxam offers to bear it, but Gamora isn't letting him have it without a fight!

24.text: Strange usually has control of every situation, but not when he's kidnapped by a group of thugs!

25.text: The adventure continues when Spidey, who's trying to make his way home after the events at Nightshade, gets mace in his eyes and dreams of fighting off a gang of demon bikers.

26.text: Wilson Fisk wants his title of “Kingpin of Crime” back.  Glorianna breaks into Daredevil’s old apartment for a news story on Murdock where Kruel attacks her.

38.text: Doc Ock's biomechanic arms are finally laid to rest.

39.text: Black Brigade has returned, and he won't stop until he exacts his revenge on every member of Force Works! His first target - Julia Carpenter, aka Spider-Woman!

40.text: The symbiote showdown continues! Law enforcement has no effect on the rampaging Carnage, which means it's time for Venom to enter the fray! But can even Venom muster the savage strength he needs to put down a monster like Carnage?

41.text: STARHAWK: SAVIOR OF THE UNIVERSE? Starhawk battles the infamous Silver Surfer!

43.text: Snakeroot threatens an innocent life and Elektra’s brother's secret grows.

44.text: With a Wakandan alliance, mutant commandos, and World Wide Web hackers at his disposal, Doom claims the American presidency with his hard-edged values.

45.text: A mission to space. An agent of the alien Shi'ar Empire. The Phoenix Saga has begun!

46.text: Scarlet Spider takes on the Sinister Six!

55.text: Spidey 2099 is captured by the Foragers after the fall of Nightshade!

57.text: The X-Men versus the brotherhood! Plus, Apocalypse plans his siege of Magneto's headquarters!

59.text: Logan finally reunites with Jean. But their reunion is cut short when Logan must do battle with a group of cyborg warriors intent on killing innocents!

61.text: Domitian's sinister plan is revealed, and the fate of Infinity Watch hangs in the balance. Can even the help of newly reformed Zakaius stop his master's evil?

63.text: Sinister has disappeared and Cyclops is given his old job. Havok's jealousy grows. How will this affect the brother's relationship and what does it hold for the future of Apocalypse's army?

64.text: Doctor Strange must destroy Salome's nest in Times Square!

67.text: Force Works and Dreamguard continue their deadly battle with the creature known only as the Orphan! Plus, a who's who of Marvel heroes remembers their fallen comrade, Wonder Man.

68.text: Carnage has had enough of captivity at Ravencroft Institute, so he's broken free and is eager to rekindle his spree of violence. One only person knows the symbiote well enough to stop him - Eddie Brock, better known to the world as Venom!

69.text: After Galactus goes missing, Starhawk makes it his mission to find out his whereabouts.

74.text: Ben Urich is attacked by Kruel and he struggles to keep his identity a secret from Daredevil.  Karen Page searches for a private investigator and Wilson Fisk keeps the city safe.

83.text: Three nations, Makhelestan, Columbia, and the United States, stand poised for revolution or revolt. Doom’s invasion of America marks a transition in his plan for world ‘liberation’.

84.text: Alien tendrils have been unleashed in the underground home of the Morlocks, can the X-Men fight this threat from another world?

85.text: The final battle between Rogue and Bella Donna! With both women depowered, who will emerge as the victor?

88.text: Elektra’s family is introduced and she self reflects as preparation for penetrating the sinister Snakeroot.

96.text: While Captain America hangs by a thread, Iron Man hatches a daring rescue plan! Into Steve Rogers subconscious he goes! Can Tony Stark revive the Sentinel of Liberty?

97.text: The Corporate Headhunter's attack has left Nightshade in shambles -- who's going to make it out alive?

99.text: When a plan to modify Sentinel programming goes completely haywire, the X-Men must engage a group of lethal Sentinels in the middle of enemy territory!
